{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c81ebf6f-3377-4b35-8d4b-e962d7152ac2","content":"Here's what I found in `my_app/views.py`:\n\n**Line 3 — `datetime.now()`** — This is a hard-coded static call that makes the function difficult to test because you can't control or predict the returned time.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nInject the clock as a dependency so tests can substitute a fixed time:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request, now=None):\n    now = now or timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\n**Benefits:**\n- **Testable** — pass a fixed `datetime` in tests.\n- **Timezone-aware** — `django.utils.timezone.now()` respects `USE_TZ`.\n\nThis is the only Python file in the project, and the only untestable static call found. Want me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d74f436a-cc3e-45a8-85bc-046e5d1d288e","outputTokens":206,"requestId":"3409:10D6CE:96E41:B7FA8:69F413A2"},"id":"534dd0b9-962f-4894-a69e-7a95064d6ce1","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:44:56.574Z","parentId":"8d9f60e1-5bf1-492d-b8fe-34f75bf19098"}
